<POSTER> &quot;Umashankar Das&quot; &lt;umashankar...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-11T02:38:00 </POSTDATE>
Hi,

POSCO has a requirement to use kandadhar mines. Mr. Jual Oram is leading an
agitation where he wants no mining in Kandadhar. I appreciate his thoughts,
that we should ensure that the waterfall in Kandadhar is not destroyed, But,
I think It would make sense if POSCO comes up with an innovative idea on how
to use the mines while retaining Kandadhar as a big tourist destination.

Perhaps, members care to point out certain thoughts on this issue....

Regards
Umashankar Das
</POST>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;Manoj Padhi&quot; &lt;manojpa...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-11T20:31:00 </POSTDATE>
Dear all:

In my opinion, there are much larger issues than saving the water fall. e.g.
Amending  MOUs for protecting state and people's interest.

Mr. Jual Oram is not raising those issues and concentrating in this
comparative smaller issue.

The same can be taken up with the ministry of tourism of GOO to develop that
as a tourist spot and leave it. However, if the whole hill is full of Ore,
digging those might damage the waterfall.

To me selling Iron Ore /ton at Rs. 27/- and damaging ecology is not worth.
Plus SEZ TAx losses . It is like Liquior Tax earning of 100+ crores is
useless ; better to stop selling of liquor there by saving lot of health
care expenses.

Either we sell Ore at a reasonable price or don't sell at all.

Thanks
Manoj padhi

