Dear Manjo ji

Though Australia has much more iron ore and coal, it's economy is thriving
on Tourism. There are many lessons to learn from them how to save our flora
and fauna. Why we are talking of Kandadhar alone. There are many other
places of tourist attraction but who bothers since those tourists are not a
lobby or big industrilists who can buy favours and influence the decision
makers.

The news is that even TATAs are also in dispute with POSCO over some of the
mining area which POSCO claims to be theirs where as TATAs claim that they
are reserved for them.

Those who see Naveen Babu as the neat and clean politicial personality needs
to review their thoughts and understand the ground reality.

Those who feel that the loot of natural resources of the state is due to the
central government's faulty policies are also living in day dreams. Even the
new decision of the Group of Ministers that has prepared a new mining policy
needs the approval of the state authorities. Why the state authorities
surrender to the dictates of the central governement to allot mining rights
for a paltry sum of money and people of the state are not only deprived of
the natural resources but also lose beautyful natural sites like Kandadhar.

About alternatives, the most serious issue that the mining department of the
state should consider is that why they allow open cast mining that destroys
hills and Flora and Fauna. Why not follow the underground mining. Since it
requires more protection and more costs, greedy mining companies manage to
bribe the authorities who permit open cast mining, which is causing huge
ecological disbalance.

Alternative is not Naveen Babu or any other Babu but awareness amongst the
people that for a paltry sum of Rs. 27/- we will not allow our resources
worth billions to be looted like this. But those blue eyed boys of Naveen
Babu may think as anti development forces. God bless them.

Pravin Patel.

