Pravin jee and et al,

Everyone who is blaming Naveen Patnaik for the poor Iron ore rate
should understand one thing clearly. The Iron-ore royalty is fixed by
Central Govt. It has been a long standing demand of mineral rich states to
change the system to ad-valorem.

As Manoj babu would say, that the above opinion is that of  BJD cadre...But,
I would challenge anybody to disprove the above facts....

The currnet mineral policy recomendation is 7.5%. I dont disagree on tourism
though. Orissa is a beautiful state. It's tourism potential is largely
unexplored. I think we have great potential to earn serious revenue
there....

Beyond that, I must also add that I realise I'm wasting my time trying to
convince people who have their own agendas. Anyhow, This mail is just for
information of people who are not aware..

Regards
Umashankar Das

