Dear Manoj ji

You have invited me to give a detailed reply. Here it goes.

The question that should arise in any body's mind is why the people of not
only Orissa but also of other adjoining tribal dominated states Jharkhand
and Chhattisgarh are so poor despite the re are abundant reserves of natural
wealth in shape of forests and Minerals in the tribal areas of our
country. No body should ignore the hard facts that there are serious
mistakes.

No body should deny that the primary duty of the state actors is to ensure
that the people of the state are living in peace and prosperity. For this
the three states under discussion have huge natural wealth that can be best
used for all round development of the state and its people. I have stated
earlier on also that with proper management of the natural resources, Orissa
can become the zero tax state.

But what happens in reality is quite contrast. State governments are
showering huge sops in the name of inviting investments. Key component of
the MOU is to allow mining rights of the natural wealth and exploitation of
natural water bodies for industrial purposes. Providing employment and
conditions for periphery development are imposed to lure the people or are
lolly pop gimmicks. I can site enough examples of blunt violations of the
vital terms of MOU but the state and its authorities have turned their blind
eyes despite drawing their attentions time and again.

No body should think by throwing the blame on the central government for a
laughable low rate of Royalty that is earned by the states. The key factors
that are in the control of the state are so vital that without the support
of the state not a single gram of mineral can be mined.

Most of the mining areas are in *Schedule V area,* where by the virtue of
Constitutional provisions, tribals enjoys full protection to their property
rights. Moreover, it is mandatory to obtain the positive resolve of tribals
duly passed in *&quot;JAN SUNWAI *[Public hearing] at a village council for any
decision to be taken be it acquisition of land or any statutory permission
including the vital environment clearances. Those who transfer the blame on
central government should understand that the district authorities of the
state are fully empowered to conduct and monitor such gram sabhas. It is
our experience so far that mostly the Gram Sabhas are held under the
fortified conditions where instead of *&quot;JAN SUNWAI&quot; *[Public hearing] it is
*&quot;GUN SUNWAI&quot;* , with extraordinary show of strength of the armed forces and
top administrative officials who are bent upon to any how manage the resolve
of the tribals despite their strong anger and protest. Even firing of live
bullets upon them is also not new. How can one transfer the blame of all
such police aided atrocities of the state committed on innocent poor tribals
to fulfill the interest of a mining contractor or we should name them as
Mining Mafias?

*We should not ignore the effects once the mining activities starts.   *The
habitats of the area are forcibly displaced even at the cost of bloodshed
and intruding in to their fundamental rights. State authorities by   bulldozing
rights of the people, buys law and order problem even at the cost of  losses
of Flora, Fauna and the hills. Reduced forest cover invites global warming,
air and water pollution is the gift to the people living in the vicinity of
those activities. Reduced forest cover, polluted atmosphere and water crisis
results in considerable economic losses in the field of Agriculture,
Horticulture and fishery. On the contrary, a handful few accumulates huge
wealth within no time, millions are left on their own.
**
*What is wrong ?*

The main reason for such disparity and causing crisis to millions for the
benefit of handful few is the result of the wrongly cultivated policies both
of the state and central government, that blindly favors the investors and
have no place or respect for the millions who are the worst sufferers.

*The main reason is that without doing proper homework, *wrong demands of
the investors are blindly accepted. This happens only in our country.
Royalties on the natural wealth is kept at laughable low rates, not by
ignorance but with the full knowledge of the authorities. They also know
very well that what they are doing is an insult to millions to fill the
coffers of an individual and share the booty. How can it be believed that
those officials who are in key posts do not know what are the international
situation and what they are doing is a big sin on the interest of the state
and its people. The real intentions of the authorities to turn blind eyes on
the international scenario can be imagined in a country which is labelled as
the most corrupt country.

*As we are discussing Iron Ore, I take it here for discussion purpose.
Situation in Bauxite is even worst.  *

India is the seventh largest producer of the Iron Ore in the world. We
were mining only 5 [five] Crore Ton of Iron before five years, which has now
crossed much over 14 [fourteen] Crore Ton by the end of year 2005. With many
more MOUs inked and new mines opened up, this figure is going to jump
considerably.

Due to huge demand of Steel all over the world, the rate of Iron Ore which
was about $ 25 before four years, has reached to US $ 86.7. [June close
precise rates ]Industry sources indicate that they should not be surprised
if the rate crosses US $ 100 in near future. What the tribal states of
Chhattigarh, Jharkhand and Orissa gets in return as Royalty is much much
less than even US $ 1. (ONE)

O.K. Automatically question arises why despite of such huge disparity
between International rates of minerals and the Royalties, it is surprising
that state governments of these three tribal states are working overtime to
dance to the tunes of the industrialists to ink MOU and allow them a free
hand. Why can't they make a pool to make a bargaining power. Why they do not
understand that they are not the owners of the huge natural wealth but are
custodian only that too for only five years and not for long 30 or 50 years
for which they grant permissions. Here is the role of the opposition
political party but here* &quot;Chor Chor Mausere Bhai&quot;* reigns supreme on
the rights of the people and forget that they are duty bound to do the
welfare of the people of the state.

*The hard facts :           *The high powered Deng Committee of Ministry of
Steel and Mines, Government of India has warned that if the present trend of
blind exploitation and export of Iron Ore continues,   there will be no more
Iron Ore left with us within next fifty years. Shri R.K. Deng has also
warned that  we shall be deep financial crisis once the Iron Ore deposits in
our country are exhausted. There is no doubt that Steel price in our country
will be too high, the closure of many steel units will be a very costly
affair to manage. It will be too costly for our country to face the likely
dangerous situation and too difficult to manage our economy with huge
population to support.

* *

*How can it be believed that our state authorities do not know that iron ore
rich nations like Ukraine, Kazakhstan, USA and China do not export any iron
ore while India exported over 90 million tones annually. &quot;Exports are
growing up at a annual rate of 15% depleting our meager ore reserves at an
alarming pace.&quot; *

Even the Indian Steel Alliance (ISA) has sought Prime Minister's
intervention to stop the continuing export of iron-ore, failing which the
growth of steel industry would be seriously jeopardized. *&quot;It is clear that
by encouraging export of iron-ore and throttling of steel exports, we are
transferring India's competitive advantage to China, Korea and Japan. In the
process we are going back to a colonial economy- becoming a mere supplier of
raw material and importer of finished product.&quot;  * ISA President Moosa Raza
wrote to the PM Manmohan Singh.

Per capita iron ore reserves of India with two major iron ore producing
countries, viz. Australia and Brazil, is negligible. *India's per capita
iron ore reserves is only 12 KG as against 333 Kg for Brazil and 1,999 Kg
for Australia.* In this reserve, only Hematite has been taken for India,

J. Mehera, Director, Essar group warned, *&quot;Indian steel industry's only
advantage vis-à-vis its international competitors is the high quality of
Indian iron-ore. This compensates for high costs of energy, coking coal,
interest rates and other financial costs. In such a situation, losing the
only advantage by allowing free exports of iron-ore will go against Indian
interests and is as good as giving your competitors a walk over. The only
way to preserve India's long term financial interest is to put a blanket ban
on export of iron-ore,&quot; *

*All this happens in the name of development where key word to lure is lolly
pop in shape of Employment; while   protests of the people are criticized as
anti developmental forces. I do not quote the figures right now but give an
example of NEELANCHAL, JINDAL, BHUSHAN STEEL, NEEPAJ STEEL, ORISSA CEMENT
LTD, etc. Those who proudly champion to shield the mischiefs of the
state should visit the above companies to find that majority of the land
losers have been cheated by not providing them any employment. Let me also
refer to the TATAs Kalinga Nagar. What the government of Orissa assures in
the name of employment opportunities for the displaced there is not seen in
the statement of a senior TATA official given under an oath. Any comments! *
